snippet.textDisplay: Still a mediocre foldable. That talk at the beginning was absolutely awful, trying to market it as an innovation while it does literally nothing different than other phones except for being foldable which is far from a big upside here. Absolutely exaggerated but sadly it will sell. It's unusable closed and still bad opened with that form factor. This is less innovating than even something simple like an always on display. The Fold wasn't great, it had an unneccesary Notch and a bad front screen. Could've easily eliminated the inner cameras with that design but no that would require actually good engineering. Also that front screen was way to small for the devices size. Which are two points they can improve on the Fold 2.But this time they didn't even try at all and that's just sad.
